content.webTitle: Golf: Flying start Clark equals record

fields.headline: Flying start Clark equals record
fields.bodyText: Tim Clark made a superb start to the defence of his South African Open title when he equalled the course record with a first-round 68 in George. Clark's five-under-par score gave him the early lead course as he took advantage of relatively calm conditions to shoot an eagle, four birdies and just one bogey. Sweden's Henrik Nystrom was in second place after a 69.
